      "releaseNotes": "New Features\n\nTime-Lapse Recording — Capture time-lapse videos in both dual lens and single lens mode. Both portrait and landscape files are saved.\nTap-to-Focus & AE/AF Lock — Tap anywhere on the preview to focus and lock exposure. Tap again to unlock. A visual indicator and AE/AF LOCK badge confirm the lock.\nPinch-to-Zoom — Smoothly zoom the back camera with a pinch gesture. Zoom is restricted to the wide lens range to prevent lens-switching conflicts.\nBitrate Quality Setting — Choose Low, Medium, or High bitrate in Settings to control file size vs. quality. \nPause & Resume — Pause your recording and resume seamlessly. Audio and video stay perfectly in sync.\n\nBug Fixes & Improvements\n\nFixed HDR metadata not being preserved in the landscape file when Apple Log is enabled.\nFixed iPhone 15 Pro incorrectly showing a hardware limits notice at 4K resolution.\nFixed audio/video desync when using the pause feature.\nFixed recordings over 20 minutes failing to save. Recordings are now limited only by available storage.",
      "version": "2.0",
      "wrapperType": "software",
      "currency": "USD",
      "description": "DualShot Recorder captures simultaneous portrait (9:16) and landscape (16:9) video from your iPhone's dual rear cameras in one take. Hit record once and get two perfectly synced files saved directly to your Photos library.\nPerfect for content creators who need both vertical and horizontal footage without filming twice.\n\nFeatures:\nSimultaneous dual-camera recording (wide + ultra wide)\nSingle lens mode with front and back camera support\n4K and 1080p resolution at 24, 30, or 60 fps\nMOV and MP4 file format options\nReal-time storage estimate so you never run out of space\nTorch/flashlight control\nNo ads, no tracking, no accounts — your footage stays on your device\n\nRequires iPhone XS or newer with dual rear cameras for dual-lens mode.",
